The Fransola Estate is found among the high vineyards of the Penedès in the municipality of Santa María de Miralles. This Fransola Estate is where we grow 25 hectares of Sauvignon Blanc used to produce our Fransola, one of our most elegant white wines. This wine is unique because it is enriched with new American oak barrel fermentation followed by four months of ageing.

In this small (29 ha.) vineyard only the most select Cabernet Sauvignon grapes are grown. These are used to make strictly limited quantities of Torres’ most prestigious red wine, now known to connoisseurs all over the world. In the Paris Wine Olympiad, the 1970 vintage triumphed over some of the most famous wines in the world, including some of the best from Bordeaux.

ShortDescription: Cotes Du Roussillon Domaine De Bila-Haut Parcellaire 750ML
LongDescription: A project of living legend Michel Chapoutier, who ran out of things to do in the Rhone and moved into the Roussillon. It offers a beautiful freshness and purity as well as fabulous notes of jammy blackberries, violets, pepper and hints of leather. Rich, concentrated and tasting like it costs four times the price, drink it over the coming 4-5 years.

A testament to Napa's grand cru vineyard site, to Kalon's signature dark-fruited, dried herb complexity is seamlessly integrated with sweet oak spices of vanilla bean and toasted almonds, sending a wave of deliciously intense flavors across the richly dense palate in a tasty expression of power and elegance.

Cinco Jotas paleta is synonomous with exquisite food. It represents an aromatic flavour and an intense capability to fall in love with the most discerning of gourmet tastes. This shoulder cut will be an essential element of your cuisine and the highlight of your selection of appetizers. Store in chilled condition after collection.

This 2017 vintage was preceded by a favourable season in the Barossa that allowed the vineyards to produce both strong yields and high quality, and in turn delivering a standout wine from this pedigree vineyard.

The Stonier Reserve Pinot Noir and Chardonnay are blends of our most prized vineyards located on the Mornington Peninsula. Complex with aromas of lemon, lime and grapefruit. Building citrus flavours on the palate, with a puckering grapefruit-like acidity. Seductive smoky notes on the nose, with a combination of lush creaminess and fresh lemon-pink grapefruit sorbet on the palate.

Featuring the best Pinot Noirs of the Montagne de Reims that gives this cuvee its unique colour and sweet intense taste. Chardonnay completes the blend and creates the elegance and sophistication expected from a champagne by Taittinger. The nose is strong and expressive, characterised by the aroma of freshly crushed wild strawberries, cherries and blackcurrants.

Castaing keeps their best meat to cook their confits. Hand salted with Salies de Bearn salt, they are slowly cooked after 4 days of maturation. It is recommended to heat them in your oven (place the skin faced to the grill till the skin becomes golden). This confit will be perfect with hash browns or ceps.
Mixture of shaved truffles peel and truffles sliced into small strips. The perfect match for your mashed potatoes, omelettes, risotto or pasta.

All the charm of a prestigious aroma is contained in our white truffle oil. Through the natural use of the white truffle - Tuber magnatum pico - olive oil gains an intense and unique fragrance: pasta or rice become incomparable and on every kind of meat and fish a few drops of truffle olive-oil will give the final touch to an unforgettable dish.
